# Strapi Project Structure

## Main Directories

- [src/api](mdc:src/api) - Contains all content types and custom APIs
- [src/components](mdc:src/components) - Reusable components for content types
- [src/extensions](mdc:src/extensions) - Extensions for Strapi core functionality
- [src/middlewares](mdc:src/middlewares) - Custom middlewares
- [src/utils](mdc:src/utils) - Utility functions and helpers
- [src/admin](mdc:src/admin) - Admin panel customizations

## API Structure

Each content type in the `src/api` directory follows this structure:

```
src/api/example/
  ├── content-types/
  │   └── example/
  │       └── schema.json    # Schema definition
  ├── controllers/
  │   └── example.ts         # Standard controller
  │   └── custom/            # Custom controllers
  ├── routes/
  │   └── example.ts         # Route definitions
  │   └── custom/            # Custom routes
  └── services/
      └── example.ts         # Standard services
      └── custom/            # Custom services
```

## Configuration

- [config](mdc:config) - Configuration files
  - Database connections
  - Server settings
  - Middleware configurations
  - Plugin configurations
